postcontent:
These are custom dies from C-H 4-D die set with two other custom seater pugs and two shell holders. 

Also one M-40A1 10 round magazine 

(110rds) brass new 

Flash Tubes 

You can also buy brass and bullets from…. http://www.cdvs.us/50-CAL-SPOTTER-C46.aspx

This is a pretty cool cartridge the spotter round was used on the 106mm recoilless rifle M-40A1 it can be used with any .50 BMG bolt face. From what I understand State that doesn’t allow .50 BMG for hunting would allow .50 Spotter cartridges. 
Reamers and head space gauge can be located from Pacific Die. Just take an old used .50 BMG barrel and set it back then re-chamber.
This is an amazing cartridge to shoot from a bolt action or semi auto rifle.. You actually stand up and fire it. Plus; as a suppressed .50 cal rifle with subsonic loads it’s unbeatable with bullets weights from 635gr to 1000grs the distance would amaze you.
As a side note: If you buy the forming die for this cartridge you can make your own .50 Spotters cases from .50 BMG

title: For Sale:  Norinco SKS Bullpup Custom lots of ammo and magazines
postcontent:
This is a Norinco SKS (Chinese) rifle that shoots the 7.62x39 round. I originally purchased this rifle when it was put together on a different plastic stock. I purchased it for 400. I installed a bullpup stock that I bought just over 200 and added a buffer recoil pad (to reduce recoil). The barrel still has a lot of life left in it. Shoots very accurately and flawlessly. 

The upgraded bullpup stock shortens the SKS about 5-6 inches from the previous length. I originally built this because I enjoy learning the different weapon platforms and I thought this would be a great shooter. Absolutely no surprises, this rifle shoots beautifully. The few times that I took it to the range, there is always a small audience behind me trying to figure out what I'm shooting. If you have friends or family that shoots, or you just want to show someone up that is different from what everyone else has, then this is the rifle for you. Or if you just like to have fun and blast away with inexpensive steel ammo, then this is also for you.

 Replacement parts for the Norinco are cheap and are plentiful because of U.S. companies making compatible parts between all of the SKS platforms for all the different countries who manufacture it. The overall recoil is very manageable, if you wanted to take someone with a small frame to range they would have a blast without any concerns of injury.

 I decided to charge 800 because although it cost me about a 100 more than what I am asking for, I figure that whoever wants to buy it will have to pay for the transfer and background check fee. So I cut the price down from 900 to 800 to help cover the cost of those transaction fees at whichever local gun shop we commit our transaction.

LSB#: 140312LF01

Make: Winchester

Model: Model 94 John Wayne Commemorative Saddle Ring Carbine

Serial Number: JW 1079

Year of Manufacture: circa 1980

Caliber: .32-40 WCF

Action Type: Lever Action with Tubular Magazine

Markings: The left side of the barrel is marked “Winchester Model 94 32-40 Win. / Made In New Haven, Conn. U.S.A. Winchester Proof Steel”. The top of the barrel is marked with a “WP” proof. The underside of the receiver is marked “JW 1079”. The right side of the barrel is marked “John Wayne Commemorative” with In-The-White lettering. The sides of the receiver are scroll engraved and with scenes from his movies. The titles of many of his western movies are engraved around the border. John Wayne’s signature is engraved on the upper tang. There is a medallion inset into the right side of the buttstock. The medallion has a portrait of John Wayne with his name written above it.

Barrel Length: About 18”

Sights / Optics: This carbine is mounted with a “U” notched semi-buckhorn rear elevator sight mounted in a dovetail. The front sight is a Patridge style blade mounted in a dovetail on the barrel.

Stock Configuration & Condition: The stocks are checkered oil finished wood. The buttstock has a carbine style blued buttplate. On the right side, it has a pewter colored medallion with a picture of John Wayne and marked with his name. There are three pores in the grain on the left side of the buttstock which do not appear to be compression marks. The checkering is sharp. The LOP measures 13” from the front of the trigger to the back of the butt plate which is in Excellent condition. The stocks rate in about Excellent overall condition.

Type of Finish: The barrel, magazine tube, loading gate, lever, trigger, buttplate and hammer are blued. The receiver, barrel bands and lever have a pewter colored plated finish.

Finish Originality: All Original

Bore Condition: The bore is bright and the rifling is sharp. There is no erosion.

Overall Condition: This rifle retains about 99% of its metal finish. The balance of the finish shows only the lightest of handling/storage marks. There is a light mark on the saddle ring. The screw heads are sharp. The markings are Clear. Overall, this rifle rates in about Excellent condition.

Mechanics: The action functions correctly. We have not fired this rifle.
Box, Paperwork & Accessories: None

Our Assessment: This rifle comes in its original factory box with a leather saddle ring thong, and paperwork. The sleeve for the box is marked “Winchester Model 94 John Wayne Commemorative” and has colored pictures of John Wayne and scenes from his movies. The sleeve shows slight fraying on its corners and a tiny tear on the side of the box at John Wayne’s neck. The inner box is Styrofoam with a Styrofoam lid and is fitted on the inside for this rifle and accessories. One end of the box has a factory label marked with the correct make, model and serial number of this rifle. The outside of the box shows light compression marks. The inside is intact and shows light oil staining from the rifle. Overall, the box and its sleeve are in Fine condition. The thong is in its factory plastic bag, and is in AS-NEW condition. The paperwork consists of a Firearms Purchase Record Card, a list of Authorized Service Centers, a Warranty, an Instruction booklet and a tag still attached to the lever loop of the rifle with a thread that gives a listing of this rifle’s specifications with a colored picture of John Wayne on the cover. The manual has a crease from being folded. The paperwork rates in about Very Good to Fine condition. A leather John Wayne Commemorative Scabbard is also included in its original cardboard box. The scabbard is marked with the Winchester logo and “WINCHESTER / MODEL 94 / JOHN WAYNE COMMEMORATIVE”. The scabbard rates in Excellent Condition. Inside the box are the two labels which have peeled off of the exterior of the scabbard box.

title: For Sale:  Colt Artillery SAA .45
postcontent:
For the very Advanced Collector, this is a 7 ½” Colt SAA in .45 Colt Caliber. Made in 1876, the pistol was originally sold to the US Military as an “Artillery” SAA. It was rejected by the Military Inspectors, and sent back to Colt. Colt re-worked the gun, and then sent it to J.P Moores Co in New York for resale on the Civilian Market. The pistol comes with a Colt factory letter that shows the shipment in 1876. Rare for an Artillery, the pistol still has a 7 ½” barrel, and the original wooden grips, there is a faint Military Inspector’s marking on the butt of the right grip. The pistol has the Colt Patent Dates, as well as a “US” marking on the left side of the receiver, it also has the # “3351” stamped in that area. The pistol has Colt’s Hartford address on top of the barrel. It also has an interesting 5 notches cut on the left side of the barrel, and also on the butt of the right grip. All the finish is missing, the pistol has patina and areas of very mild freckling, the grips show commensurate wear, the bore is somewhat dark with some visible marking. The cylinder retains all 4 cocks and locks up tightly. This is a excellent Colt SAA that will enhance a great collection! This is an antique firearm – if it is legal for you to own this weapon where you live, and with a copy of your Drivers License, establishing that you are over age 21, I can ship the rifle direct to your home, an FFL License is not required.

Please be sure it is legal for you to own prior to bidding. Buyer to pay $35 shipping/insurance. Payment via cashier bank transfer or USPS money order.
